    "It is this combination of GS-type variables for AdS 3 √ó S 3 and (topologically-twisted) RNS-like variables for T 4 from which the name \"hybrid\" is derived.Following [12,40] and working at generic k ‚àà N, there is a (small) N = 4 topological algebra in the string theory generated byT = T W ZW + T œÉ + T œÅ + T C, G -= e -iœÉ + G - C, G + = -e -2œÅ-iœÉ P + e -œÅ Q + e iœÉ T + G + C, G+ = e œÅ+iH + e œÅ+iœÉ G+ C, G-= -e -3œÅ-2iœÉ-iH P + e -2œÅ-iœÉ-iH Q -e -œÅ-iH T -e -œÅ-iœÉ G- C, J = 1 2 ‚àÇ(œÅ + iœÉ) + J C, J ¬±¬± = e ¬±œÅ¬±iœÉ¬±iH,(2.10)wherefoot_6 T = T W ZW - 1 2 (‚àÇ(œÅ + iœÉ)) 2 + 1 2 ‚àÇ 2 (œÅ + iœÉ).The operator T W ZW is the Sugawara energy momentum tensor associated to the WZW model for psu(1, 1|2) k and similarly P and Q depend only on the WZW variables.",
